<p>had orders to put us on another train, &amp; so off we went to Poperhinge the renowned Belgian town she is a good big place &amp; shows a few signs of being knocked about by shell fire, here we heard the guns again after an absence of a fortnight from them, I need scarcely say they were not particularly cheerful, especially in our present state of mind, for you can guess how we felt didn't give a cuss what happened.</p>
<p>We saw some of our chaps about here &amp; learned that the Brigade was about 4 miles out of the town, we had to report from here to Divisional Hqr's so off we</p>
